<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Quick Setup - {{.RepoName}}</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: -apple-system, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; padding: 40px; background: #f6f8fa; color: #24292e; }
        .container { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; background: white; border: 1px solid #e1e4e8; border-radius: 6px; padding: 32px; }
        h1 { border-bottom: 1px solid #eaecef; padding-bottom: 10px; }
        code { background: #f3f3f3; padding: 4px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-family: monospace; }
        pre { background: #f6f8fa; padding: 16px; border-radius: 6px; overflow: auto; border: 1px solid #ddd; }
        .setup-section { margin-top: 24px; }
        .back-link { text-decoration: none; color: #0366d6; font-size: 0.9rem; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <a href="/dashboard" class="back-link">← Back to Dashboard</a>
        <h1>Quick setup — if you’ve done this kind of thing before</h1>
        
        <div class="setup-section">
            <p><strong>Create a new repository on the command line</strong></p>
            <pre>
echo "# {{.RepoName}}" >> README.md
git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin ssh://git@yourdomain.com:{{.SSHPort}}/{{.Username}}/{{.RepoName}}.git
git push -u origin main</pre>
        </div>

        <div class="setup-section">
            <p><strong>…or push an existing repository from the command line</strong></p>
            <pre>
git remote add origin ssh://git@yourdomain.com:{{.SSHPort}}/{{.Username}}/{{.RepoName}}.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main</pre>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>